{"lemma":"بَذْرِ","slug":"بَذْرِ","root":"ب.ذ.ر","root_slug":"ب-ذ-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ذ-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2086","","n2088","n2089","n2091"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B0%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to seed"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to extend, reveal, circulate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to use something in wasteful manner; to use to no purpose, for inadequate result, extravagantly","examples":[{"text":"وَآتِ ذَا ٱلْقُرْبَىٰ حَقَّهُ وَٱلْمِسْكِينَ وَٱبْنَ ٱلسَّبِيلِ وَلَا تُبَذِّرْ تَبْذِيرًا ۝ إِنَّ ٱلْمُبَذِّرِينَ كَانُوا إِخْوَانَ ٱلشَّيَاطِينِ وَكَانَ ٱلشَّيْطَانُ لِرَبِّهِ كَفُورًا"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to gradually waste something"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"seeds","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"seed","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"seedling","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pips, pits, (fruit) stones","tags":["collective","in-plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ب ذ ر (b ḏ r). Possibly related to Aramaic בדר (“to scatter, to disperse”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2086","headword_ar":"بَذَرَ","root":"b*r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, A, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*orN","text_ar":"بَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sowed"},{"kind":"text","text":"seed; (S, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he cast"},{"kind":"text","text":"grain"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the ground to sow it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he cast"},{"kind":"text","text":"grain upon the ground,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scattering it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he scattered"},{"kind":"text","text":"seed (T, MF)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the ground;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b*~r","text_ar":"بذّر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [but app. in an intensive sense,] (MF,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabo*iyrN","text_ar":"تَبْذِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, MF) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabo*irapN","text_ar":"تَبْذِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T:) this is the primary signification. (MF.) ―         -b2-  Also, (M,) inf. n. as above, (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sowed"},{"kind":"text","text":"land; (M, L, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b*~r","text_ar":"بذّر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabo*iyrN","text_ar":"تَبْذِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, K.) ―         -b3-  Also, (M,) inf. n. as above, (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He scattered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) a thing; (M;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b*~r","text_ar":"بذّر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he scattered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed, much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabo*iyrN","text_ar":"تَبْذِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*ara A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"بَذَرَ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxaloqi","text_ar":"الخَلْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A,) inf. n. as above, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God scattered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed, mankind"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A) in the earth. (A.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*ara AlkalaAma","text_ar":"بَذَرَ الكَلَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He disseminated, scattered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diffused, talk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"بَيْنَ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mankind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as seed is scattered: (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b*~rhu","text_ar":"بذّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did so much."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*arati AlA^aroDu","text_ar":"بَذَرَتِ الاَرْضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A,) aor. as above, (M,) and so the inf. n., (M, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The land put forth its plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, M, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a scattered state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, M, A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put forth its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*or","text_ar":"بَذْر"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*ura","text_ar":"بَذُرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*aArapN","text_ar":"بَذَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He divulged what was secret; he revealed what he had heard."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*ira","text_ar":"بَذِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*arN","text_ar":"بَذَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He talked much; was loquacious."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","A","Msb","K","MF","M","L","TA","As"]},{"entry_id":"n2088","headword_ar":"بَذْرٌ","root":"b*r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bu*orN","text_ar":"بُذْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) the former either an inf. n. used as a proper subst. or of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEolN","text_ar":"فَعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Grain that is set apart for sowing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any seed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grain that is sown;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bizorN","text_ar":"بِزْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bazorN","text_ar":"بَزْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Kh, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grain such as wheat, that is sown;"},{"kind":"text","text":"distinguished from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bzr","text_ar":"بزر"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is applied to the seed of sweet-smelling plants and of leguminous herbs: and this distinction commonly obtains: (Msb:) or [so accord. to the M, but in the K “and,”] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first that comes forth, of seed-produce and of leguminous and other plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as long as it has but two leaves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*orN","text_ar":"بَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage, when just come forth from the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as has assumed a colour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shown its kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"species:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bu*uwrN","text_ar":"بُذُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi*aArN","text_ar":"بِذَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*orN","text_ar":"بَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Progeny;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bu*aArapN","text_ar":"بُذَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^in~a h`w^ulaA='i laba*oru sawo'K","text_ar":"اِنَّ هٰوُلَا=ءِ لَبَذْرُ سَوْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily these are a progeny of evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an evil progeny."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A. *)"}],"source_refs":["M","Msb","Kh","K"]},{"entry_id":"n2089","headword_ar":"بُذْرٌ","root":"b*r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*orN","text_ar":"بَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n2091","headword_ar":"بَذِرٌ","root":"b*r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tibo*aArapN","text_ar":"تِبْذَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also, (M, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayo*aArN","text_ar":"بَيْذَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayo*aArap","text_ar":"بَيْذَارَة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tibo*aArN","text_ar":"تِبْذَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayo*aAraAniy~N","text_ar":"بَيْذَارَانِيٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) (tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who talks much; loquacious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hu*arapN bu*arapN","text_ar":"هُذَرَةٌ بُذَرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, M) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayo*aArapN bayo*aArapN","text_ar":"هَيْذَارَةٌ بَيْذَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"irrationally,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vainly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"frivolously, loquacious; a great babbler."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*uwrN","text_ar":"بَذُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaEaAmN ba*irN","text_ar":"طَعَامٌ بَذِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wheat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bu*aArap","text_ar":"بُذَارَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"increase, redundance, exuberance, plenty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, * M, L, K. *)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","IDrd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}